      "writtenOn": "2020-08-19T09:40:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is a bit tricky condition because (sc.patterns !\u003d nil \u0026\u0026 ...) is evaluated for two cases, hostBlock and notInBlock.\n\nFor explicitness, I recommend using a switch statement, e.g.\n\n switch sc.blockType {\n   case notInBlock:\n     // Always accept.\n   case hostBlock:\n     if !matchHost(inputHostName, sc.patterns) {\n       return \"\", \"\"\n     }\n   case matchBlock:\n     // Always reject - match is not supported.\n     return \"\", \"\"\n }",
      "range": {
